info.author: Keyphrene
info.description:
Naja is a download manager and a website grabber written in Python/wxPython. 
You can add some
plugins (newsreader, newsposter, client FTP, client WebDAV) and take control
of your downloads from your office. Naja supports proxy (HTTP, HTTPS,
FTP, SOCKS v4a, SOCKS v5), and use some authentication methods.
The downloading maybe achieved by splitting  the file being downloaded
into several parts and downloading these parts  at the same time (HTTP,
HTTPS, FTP). Donwload speeds are increased by downloading the file
from the mirrors sites, when the sites propose it.
        
Others features:
 Csv filter
 Cheksums (CRC32, MD5, SHA1)
 newsreader, newsposter (uue, yEnc)
 CGI & WebDAV Server (Only PROPFIND method for the moment)
 Web Admin Interface
 basic and digest authentication for client and server
        
Naja is available for download from the Keyphrene web site and exists under 
Windows, Linux and MacOS X:
http://www.keyphrene.com/products/naja
